This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and deep learning techniques for sentiment analysis, which are typically covered in the arXiv category cs.CL (Computation and Language). The use of regularization techniques and pre-trained word embeddings also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the use of PyTorch as the implementation framework suggests a focus on neural networks (cs.NE) and computer vision (cs.CV) applications.
